{"questionId":"1250006","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Show that the total kinetic energy <em>E</em><sub>k</sub> of the sphere when it rolls, without slipping, at speed <em>v</em> is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{E_{\\text{K}}} = \\frac{7}{{10}}m{v^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>E</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>K</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>7</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>E</em><sub>k</sub> = <em>E</em><sub>k</sub> linear + <em>E</em><sub>k</sub> rotational</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">OR</span></strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{E_{\\text{k}}} = \\frac{1}{2}m{v^2} + \\frac{1}{2}I{\\omega ^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>E</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>k</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>I</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>ω</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></span><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">&nbsp; ✔</span></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{1}{2}m{v^2} + \\frac{1}{2} \\times \\frac{2}{5}m{r^2} \\times {\\left( {\\frac{v}{r}} \\right)^2}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n    <mn>5</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>v</mi>\n            <mi>r</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> &nbsp;<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">✔</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{7}{{10}}m{v^2}\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>7</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>»</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Answer is given in the question so check working is correct at each stage.</span></span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"1250006","referenceCode":"19M.2.HL.TZ2.9a","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Show that the total kinetic energy Ek of the sphere when it rolls, without slipping, at speed v is E K = 7 10 m v 2 .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A.4 Rigid body mechanics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}